No fewer than 25 people were killed in an attack by gunmen in several villages in three Local Government Areas of Benue State. It was gathered that several others were wounded. Daily Post reports that a resident in the area, Mr. Tewase Hembe said the three local government areas are Guma, Logo, and Tarka. He said the LGAâ€™s came under severe gunfire between 9 pm on Monday night and 4 am on Tuesday, leaving 15 corpses in Tyotugh community in Tarka LGA while nine other dead bodies were recovered from Guma and one, a traditional ruler from Logo. He said the search for more bodies has continued with fear that casualty figures could be higher. Chairman of Guma LGA, Caleb Aba who confirmed the incident said seven people were killed in one swoop at Tse-Sumaka village near branch Umenger in Mbadwem council ward of Guma. Meanwhile, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), SP Catherine Anene is yet to confirm the attack.